= Developing with the Eclipse IDE =

	1. Install the PyDev extension in eclipse
	2. Install MercurialEclipse
	3. Create a new Mercurial project that clones the repo
	4. Right-click on the project: PyDev > Set as Pydev Project
	5. Right-click on the project: PyDev > Set as Django Project
	6. Close Eclipse
	7. Run /my/local/python bootstrap.py from the new project directory
	8. Run bin/buildout - this will install all the required dependencies and reconfigure pydev
	9. Restart Eclipse
	10. Run the tool using run as "Pydev: Django"
	
Reference:

	http://pydev.org/manual_101_project_conf2.html